questions.question:
The P and V operations on counting semaphores, where s is a counting semaphore, are defined as follows:
P(s): s = s - 1;
      if (s < 0) then wait;
V(s): s = s + 1;
      if (s <= 0) then wake up process waiting on s;

Assume that P_b and V_b, the wait and signal operations on binary semaphores, are provided. Two binary semaphores z_1 and z_2 are used to implement P(s) and V(s) as follows:

P(s):
  P_b(z_1);
  s = s - 1;
  if (s < 0)
  { V_b(z_1); P_b(z_2); }
  else V_b(z_1);

V(s):
  P_b(z_1);
  s = s + 1;
  if (s <= 0) V_b(z_2);
  else V_b(z_1);

The initial values of z_1 and z_2 are, respectively:
A. 0 and 0
B. 0 and 1
C. 1 and 0
D. 1 and 1
